1 the salaries and expenses of the attorneys they employ within the limits of
2 legislative appropriations.
3 c. The attorneys that represent these entities must be special assistant attorneys
4 general appointed by the attorney general pursuant to this section. Absent good
5 cause, the attorney general shall appoint as special assistant attorneys general
6 licensed attorneys selected by these entities. The attorney general may revoke
7 the appointment only for good cause or upon the request of the entity. Good
8 cause means an inadequate level of experience, competence, or ethical
9 standards.
10 2. Notwithstanding any other provisions of this section, if an attorney is employed by the
11 governor, state auditor, or ethics commission, the attorney general may not:
12 a. Refuse to appoint the attorney as a special assistant attorney general upon
13 request from the entity; or
14 b. Revoke the appointment as special assistant attorney general absent good cause
15 and upon the request of the entity.
16 3. The powers conferred upon special assistant attorneys general are the same as are
17 exercised by the regular assistant attorneys general, unless the powers are limited
18 specifically by the terms of the appointment. Except as otherwise provided by this
19 section, an appointment is revocable at the pleasure of the attorney general. The
20 appointment may be made with or without compensation, and when compensation is
21 allowed by the attorney general for services performed, the compensation must be
22 paid out of the funds appropriated therefor.
23 3.4. The attorney general may require payment for legal services rendered by any
24 assistant or special assistant attorney general to any state official, board, department,
25 agency, or commission and those entities shall make the required payment to the
26 attorney general. Moneys received by the attorney general in payment for legal
27 services rendered must be deposited into the attorney general's operating fund.
28 General fund moneys may not be utilized for the payment of legal services provided by
29 the attorneys employed by the attorney general, except for those payments required of
30 the department of health and human services, department of environmental quality,
31 and the state hospital.
